This position will supervise the activities of students enrolled in the in-person
option for schooling at Dove Academy. Student supervision aides will
supervise students in a classroom environment. This position will be Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday (no work on Wednesday) and will be from 8AM-4PM.

Qualifications:
¬ª Demonstrated competence working with children.
¬ª Computer literate.
¬ª Excellent verbal and written expression.
¬ª Strong interpersonal skills.
¬ª Works well in a collaborative environment.

Please contact Erin Jeffrey, Human Resources Generalist directly with questions at erinjeffrey@choiceschools.com

Hello Dove Families,

We are excited to get back to school and return our scholars to learning. Safety will remain our number one concern but we are still prepared to provide you with a top-level educational experience and support for your learners. In this survey, you will be asked to MAKE A CHOICE for each of your learners as to how you want them to receive this education. Your choice will allow us to better prepare for school and will be their Learning Path for the year. Dove's certified teaching staff will offer instruction using our curriculum and technology resources in a Face to Face and a Virtual learning option.

text:
Hello Dove Families,

We are excited to get back to school and return our scholars to learning. Safety will remain our number one concern but we are still prepared to provide you with a top-level educational experience and support for your learners. In this survey, you will be asked to MAKE A CHOICE for each of your learners as to how you want them to receive this education. Your choice will allow us to better prepare for school and will be their Learning Path for the year. Dove's certified teaching staff will offer instruction using our curriculum and technology resources in a Face to Face and a Virtual learning option.

Hello #DoveNation!

On Tuesday, Gov. Whitmer announced the "Return to School Road Map." Our team is currently updating our plans and will be sharing and seeking feedback from all of you throughout the month of July. Thank you for all of your support during this time of uncertainty and know that we want nothing more than to see each of our students' smiling faces in the fall!

In the meantime, check your Class Dojo because a more detailed letter was just sent out. We are doing our very best to openly communicate and do what is best for our students. Our work will continue in the coming weeks as we utilize the Roadmap.

Have a great 4th of July!

Your Dove Team

Good Evening #DoveNation!

Due to the low number of grab and go meals being picked up over the past few weeks we will no longer be distributing meals Tuesday - Thursday.

For families that are still in need for meal pick ups the Detroit Parks and Recreation department is offering free breakfast and lunch pick up at 3 of their locations.

Adams Butzel Recreation Center, 10500 Lyndon
Farwell Recreation Center, 2711 E. Outer Drive
Kemeny Recreation Center, 2260 S. Fort Street.

Parents and children can pick up breakfast and lunch Monday through Thursday between 8:30 a.m. and 1:30 p.m. On Fridays, they can request additional meals to get them through the weekend.

Dear #DoveNation Families, at this time we are following the direction of the Governor regarding the Coronavirus (COVID-19). Dove Academy will be closed Monday, March 16th until Sunday, April 5th in an attempt to slow the spread of the virus.

On Monday, March 16th, all Pre-K-8th grade families will be receiving messages from teachers via Class Dojo with online resources and materials to continue the learning process.

If you do not have access to technology please stop by the school on Tuesday, March 17th or Wednesday, March 18th from 9am- 12pm to pick up hard copies of the learning packets.

We appreciate your patience and flexibility during this trying time and will keep you updated as we receive more information.

Sincerely,
Mr. Brooks
